About the Business:
Lower Manhattan Pain and Wellness Center is a top-rated rehabilitation, sports medicine, and wellness practice that offers a comprehensive range of integrative medical services for every member of your family. Located in Chinatown, New York City, the practice serves patients of all ages from the greater New York City area.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Led by board-certified physiatrist Josephine Huang, MD, the talented practitioners at Lower Manhattan Pain and Wellness Center take a holistic, multidisciplinary approach to health and wellness that encourages you to be an active participant in your own care.&nbsp;

The team at Lower Manhattan Pain and Wellness Center uses acupuncture, physical therapy, and medication to relieve or resolve neuralgia, joint, neck, and back pain, and other forms of musculoskeletal pain. They also provide post-op rehabilitation services for patients following orthopedic surgery and neurosurgery.&nbsp;

On top of delivering attentive pain evaluations, targeted treatment solutions, key lifestyle recommendations, and practical advice for routine health problems, they offer a complete menu of supportive services ranging from stress management to exercise counseling.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Physical medicine and rehabilitation aim to optimize your health as well as your quality of life, and the team at Lower Manhattan Pain and Wellness Center is dedicated to providing the kind of top-quality care and effective pain solutions that help you avoid future illness and injury.&nbsp;...

About the Practice
&nbsp;
43rd St. Physical Medicine &amp; Rehabilitation offers cutting-edge solutions for chronic pain. Located in the Theater District of Manhattan, New York City, the spacious office delivers a wide range of treatments. The 43rd St. Physical Medicine &amp; Rehabilitation team is proud to offer state-of-the-art chiropractic care for patients of all ages.
43rd St. Physical Medicine &amp; Rehabilitation offers on-site ultrasound and X-rays. The team uses imaging tests to identify the source of patients' pain to develop customized treatment plans. They tailor each treatment to meet patients' unique needs.&nbsp;
Available treatments include physical therapy, massage therapy, and acupuncture. The staff also offer trigger point injections and custom orthotics. These treatments provide lasting relief to patients struggling with headaches, hip pain, knee pain, or back pain. Providers also use the Graston® Technique to help break down scar tissue and improve physical function.&nbsp;
43rd St. Physical Medicine &amp; Rehabilitation is proud to be a trusted provider for professional athletes, actors, and dancers. The team has unmatched expertise in treating sports injuries and overuse injuries. They enjoy helping patients resolve their pain and return to work quickly.&nbsp;
